Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the rice.

When boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}, pop back in the pan, cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}.

Halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Slice the @Sugar Snap Peas{80%g} in half lengthways.

Roughly chop the @Coriander{1}(stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. When the oil is hot, add the red onion and pepper and stir-fry until slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the veg have softened add the @King Prawns{150%g} and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%packet} to the pan. Cook stirring frequently until the prawns are cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when they are pink on the outside and opaque all the way through.

Add the sugar snaps to the pan, lower the heat and stir in the @Hoisin Sauce{64%g} and @Soy Sauce{25%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season the sauce with salt and pepper if needed. Stir though half the coriander.

Share the rice between your bowls and spoon your sticky prawns on top.

Sprinkle over the remaining coriander. Enjoy!